            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "\u00a9 2014 The Author. Motivation: Kablammo is a web-based application that produces interactive, vector-based visualizations of sequence alignments generated by BLAST. These visualizations can illustrate many features, including shared protein domains, chromosome structural modifications and genome misassembly. Availability and implementation: Kablammo can be used at http://kablammo.wasmuthlab.org. For a local installation, the source code and instructions are available under the MIT license at http://github.com/jwintersinger/kablammo.",
